725
00:37:21,839 --> 00:37:26,242
May I ask, who goes out
on the battlefield
without their boots?

726
00:37:26,310 --> 00:37:27,709
Maybe someone has bunions.

727
00:37:27,778 --> 00:37:30,008
Bunions, Gus? Really?
That's what you're bringing
to the table?

728
00:37:30,081 --> 00:37:31,378
I'm trying to solve
a murder here.

729
00:37:31,449 --> 00:37:33,076
I deal with bunions
at work every day, Shawn.

730
00:37:33,150 --> 00:37:34,708
They hurt...
They hurt people.

731
00:37:34,785 --> 00:37:36,047
That's a perfectly
logical assumption.

732
00:37:36,120 --> 00:37:39,248
Oh, yeah?
What about this?
No tunic.

733
00:37:42,026 --> 00:37:43,687
This is Mahoney's!

734
00:37:47,031 --> 00:37:48,020
What?

735
00:37:50,701 --> 00:37:52,293
The brass button.

736
00:37:53,337 --> 00:37:54,861
(WHISPERING)
Mahoney did it.

737
00:37:56,641 --> 00:37:59,075
That's why he had
that sticky musket.

738
00:37:59,143 --> 00:38:01,611
He must've gotten sap on it
from that notch in the tree.

739
00:38:01,679 --> 00:38:05,615
Wait. This doesn't track.
Why kill Sally? She's hot,
they're friends.

740
00:38:05,683 --> 00:38:06,945
She even wrote
his insurance policy.

741
00:38:07,018 --> 00:38:08,781
(EXPLODING)

742
00:38:08,853 --> 00:38:10,320
That was C-<i>4</i>!

743
00:38:10,554 --> 00:38:13,079
That didn't come
from the battlefield,
it came from the south.

744
00:38:14,358 --> 00:38:15,416
I solved the crime.
No, I did.

745
00:38:15,493 --> 00:38:16,551
I said it first.
I identified the uniform.

746
00:38:16,627 --> 00:38:19,118
I found the button near
the tree. I said it first.
Tap, tap, no take-backs.

747
00:38:19,196 --> 00:38:20,663
That's not fair, Shawn.
I was identifying
the C-<i>4</i> sound.

748
00:38:20,731 --> 00:38:23,666
Dude, you snooze
you lose, Gus.
I don't have to tell you.

749
00:38:24,402 --> 00:38:26,233
That manhole we found
connects to the sewer.

750
00:38:26,304 --> 00:38:29,068
It's going to lead us right
to our killer. Let's go.

751
00:38:29,140 --> 00:38:30,198
We're going in by ourself?

752
00:38:30,274 --> 00:38:31,741
What, are you crazy?

753
00:38:46,257 --> 00:38:48,748
Where you going, Mahoney?
Hey, Griff!

754
00:38:48,893 --> 00:38:50,656
Hello, boys.

755
00:38:51,062 --> 00:38:53,929
Back off. Back off.

756
00:38:54,598 --> 00:38:57,897
Back off. This gun is loaded.

757
00:38:57,968 --> 00:38:59,936
(GUNS COCKING)

758
00:39:00,404 --> 00:39:02,895
Yes, but mine are
so much bigger.

759
00:39:03,607 --> 00:39:04,801
CARLTON: Get out of the way,
I'm coming through.

760
00:39:04,875 --> 00:39:07,537
What the hell is
going on down here?

761
00:39:08,179 --> 00:39:09,806
Colonel,

762
00:39:09,880 --> 00:39:12,144
arrest this traitor.

763
00:39:14,518 --> 00:39:17,078
I'll have that weapon,
Captain.

764
00:39:24,562 --> 00:39:28,157
Okay, hold on,
I'm gonna need you
to walk me through this.

765
00:39:28,232 --> 00:39:29,927
Mahoney blew up
his own vault?

766
00:39:30,000 --> 00:39:32,833
MAHONEY: That is an absolutely
outrageous...
Shut up!

767
00:39:32,903 --> 00:39:35,030
Not only did he blow it up,

768
00:39:35,272 --> 00:39:37,740
he used the battle as a cover
to rob his own store.

769
00:39:37,808 --> 00:39:41,300
Then, he'd collect a multi-
million dollar insurance
policy in a couple of weeks,

770
00:39:41,379 --> 00:39:43,540
then slip back
to the battle
during the cannon fire

771
00:39:43,614 --> 00:39:46,174
with no one ever
being the wiser.

772
00:39:47,651 --> 00:39:52,088
Oh, ye immoral
man of low fiber!

773
00:39:52,156 --> 00:39:53,555
You should really
eat more bran.

774
00:39:53,624 --> 00:39:54,989
I want to see my lawyer.

775
00:39:55,059 --> 00:39:56,583
In due time.

776
00:39:56,660 --> 00:40:00,152
Wait, but I still
don't understand.
Why kill Nelson Poe?

777
00:40:00,231 --> 00:40:02,358
That is the rub, isn't it?

778
00:40:02,433 --> 00:40:04,799
Sally Reynolds was
the intended target.

779
00:40:04,869 --> 00:40:06,860
The question is why?

780
00:40:08,205 --> 00:40:10,105
Hi, Juliet.
Got your message.

781
00:40:10,174 --> 00:40:11,300
What the hell is going on?

782
00:40:11,375 --> 00:40:12,899
Oh, I can see it
clearly now.

783
00:40:12,977 --> 00:40:15,639
Sally wrote Mahoney's
multi-million dollar
insurance policy.

784
00:40:15,713 --> 00:40:17,237
That means she...

785
00:40:18,082 --> 00:40:20,482
She was in on the fraud
from the start.

786
00:40:20,551 --> 00:40:21,984
That's a lie.

787
00:40:22,052 --> 00:40:25,818
But Mahoney here didn't want
to share those millions,
so he gets an idea.

788
00:40:25,890 --> 00:40:28,415
What if sweet, sweet Sally
with the filthy mouth

789
00:40:28,492 --> 00:40:30,926
and the bedroom eyes
had a little accident

790
00:40:30,995 --> 00:40:33,327
out on the battlefield
during the rehearsal?

791
00:40:33,397 --> 00:40:35,627
You mean Griffin tried
to kill me?
That's right.

792
00:40:35,699 --> 00:40:37,860
This is a lie.
You are fabricating
everything you're saying.

793
00:40:37,935 --> 00:40:39,266
Now you hold on a second,
Mr. Mahoney.

794
00:40:39,336 --> 00:40:42,703
Oh, hey, Gus, you see,
when Nelson rolled
down the creek bed

795
00:40:42,773 --> 00:40:44,468
<i>and landed too close</i>
<i>to the river, he looked up</i>

796
00:40:44,542 --> 00:40:47,340
<i>and he saw Griffin</i>
<i>in the tree with his trusty</i>
<i>musket, who said,</i>

797
00:40:47,411 --> 00:40:50,869
"Griffin, now you must
kill Nelson Poe

798
00:40:50,948 --> 00:40:53,883
"to keep his
stinking mouth shut."

799
00:40:54,552 --> 00:40:55,917
Told you you had
the wrong person, Lassiter.

800
00:40:55,986 --> 00:40:57,180
I know.

801
00:40:57,388 --> 00:41:01,518
Detective O'Hara...
Lose the hoop skirt
before you hurt someone.

802
00:41:01,592 --> 00:41:03,924
Read 'em their rights
and book ' em.

803
00:41:06,096 --> 00:41:07,927
CARLTON: Excuse me, gentlemen.

804
00:41:09,033 --> 00:41:12,093
Hey, it was good work,
Detective. We got 'em.

805
00:41:12,169 --> 00:41:13,193
"We"?

806
00:41:13,270 --> 00:41:15,067
We're a team, right?

807
00:41:23,747 --> 00:41:27,649
SHAWN: Gus. When we grow up,
think I'll ever be
as cool as you?

808
00:41:27,718 --> 00:41:30,186
You're better at kickball.

809
00:41:30,254 --> 00:41:31,778
Not what I asked.

810
00:41:32,556 --> 00:41:33,750
We talking about
your dad again?

811
00:41:33,824 --> 00:41:35,291
Mmm-hmm.

812
00:41:35,359 --> 00:41:37,884
Come on, dude.
The guy respects you.

813
00:41:37,962 --> 00:41:39,429
Not like he does you.

814
00:41:39,497 --> 00:41:40,691
I'm not his son.

815
00:41:40,764 --> 00:41:43,858
I mean, he might like me okay,
but he loves you.

816
00:41:44,768 --> 00:41:46,167
Did he say that?

817
00:41:46,237 --> 00:41:47,670
No.

818
00:41:47,738 --> 00:41:49,797
Then how can you be sure?

819
00:41:49,874 --> 00:41:52,399
You mean he's never said it?

820
00:41:52,476 --> 00:41:54,808
Come on, Gus. We're guys.

821
00:42:01,785 --> 00:42:03,252
Charge!
Charge!

822
00:42:13,163 --> 00:42:16,655
<i>In between the lines</i>
<i>there's a lot of obscurity</i>

823
00:42:16,834 --> 00:42:20,235
<i>I'm not inclined</i>
<i>to resign to maturity</i>

824
00:42:20,404 --> 00:42:23,567
<i>If it's all right</i>
<i>then you're all wrong</i>

825
00:42:23,641 --> 00:42:27,008
<i>But why bounce around</i>
<i>to the same damn song?</i>

826
00:42:28,445 --> 00:42:32,643
<i>You'd rather run</i>
<i>when you can't crawl</i>

827
00:42:34,618 --> 00:42:37,951
<i>I know, you know</i>
<i>That I'm not telling the truth</i>

828
00:42:38,155 --> 00:42:41,420
<i>I know, you know</i>
<i>They just don't have any proof</i>

829
00:42:41,492 --> 00:42:44,484
<i>Embrace the deception</i>
<i>Learn how to bend</i>

830
00:42:44,628 --> 00:42:48,587
<i>Your worst inhibitions</i>
<i>tend to psych you out</i>
<i>in the end</i>

831
00:42:48,666 --> 00:42:50,634
<i>I know, you know</i>

832
00:42:52,169 --> 00:42:53,966
<i>I know, you know</i>

